	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Whoops, I figured out why I'd been having trouble running my 32kB banked code on this PCB.  Design flaw in the schematic.  I had the right idea, almost. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />  Live and learn.  The (currently untested) fix is to cut a trace and add a wire.
<br />
<br />Doesn't affect 16kB mode of course, which is the main point of the design.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


